NOTES:(in english & spanish)

  [1]: Los 90 minutos reglamentarios finalizaron 0-0. Se realizaron 2 tiempos suplementarios,
       el primero de 15 minutos y el segundo de 6 minutos, éste por falta de luz.
  [2]: First match played with the "Albiceleste" (light blue/white vertical stripes) shirt.
  [3]: Match defined in supplementary time.
  [4]: Dissident Argentine national team.
  [5]: Partido oficializado por FIFA.
  [6]: There was an addition of 7 minutes because of lack of light.
  [7]: Este partido se había suspendido el día anterior a los 6 minutos por invasión
       del público. Continuado al día siguiente.
  [8]: Los 90 minutos reglamentarios finalizaron 1-1. Se realizaron 2 tiempos
       suplementarios de 15 minutos cada uno y se mantuvo invariable el marcador.
       Como caso extraño en el historial futbolístico, se jugaron otros 2 tiempos
       suplementarios. Pero, al comenzar la segunda parte de esta nueva prolongación
       ('139), por falta de luz, debió suspenderse, manteniéndose el 1-1. No se
       completaron los minutos que restaban del cotejo suspendido, sino que se convino
       jugar un segundo partido 10 días después.
  [9]: Se dió por finalizado a los 52 minutos por lluvia.
 [10]: This match was suspended at the 86 minutes.
 [11]: This match started with 8 players on each side. On the evening before
       the match, a local newspapers had insulted the Brazilians ("macacos").
       Several players refused to enter the field and therefore Brazil only had
       8 players; Argentina, as a gesture of honor, then also played with 3 less.
 [12]: According to some sources is the Asunción Combined.
 [13]: Suspendido a los 79 minutos porque el equipo paraguayo abandonó el campo de juego 
       en protesta por la sanción del penal.
 [14]: Dissident Uruguayan national team (Federación Uruguaya de Foot-Ball).
 [15]: Este partido fue suspendido a los 4 minutos debido a la invasión del público a la cancha.
       Reprogramado para el 2 de Octubre.
 [16]: Suspendido a los 86 minutos por haberse retirado del campo de juego el equipo uruguayo.
 [17]: Also it was got in contest the City of Lima Fourth Centenary Cup.
 [18]: The Brazilian national team scored its third goal when the Argentine team
       had left the field because of problems.
 [19]: This match was suspended after 41 minutes when the Chileans left the field,
       in disagreement with a decision of the referee; CSF decided to award both
       points to Argentina.
       This match is counted for the statistics as drawn.
 [20]: This match was suspended after 23 minutes because of the rain.
 [21]: According to some sources is the Guanabara Team.
 [22]: Triumvirate composed by Victorio Spinetto, José Della Torre and José Barreiro.
 [23]: According to some sources is the Guanabara Team.
 [24]: According to some sources is the Minas Gerais Team.
 [25]: This match was decided by penalties. Argentina won 4-1.
 [26]: This match was decided by penalties to decide the possession of the cup.
       Paraguay won 3-1.
 [27]: El rival se presentó como Liga de Irlanda pero fueron oficializados por la FIFA.
 [28]: This match was decided by penalties. Argentina won 8-7.
 [29]: Partido suspendido a los 85 minutos por invasión del público.
 [30]: This match was decided by penalties after extra time. Argentina won 3-2.
 [31]: This match was decided by penalties after extra time. Argentina won 4-3.
 [32]: This match was decided by penalties after extra time to decide the possession
       of the cup. Argentina won 5-4.
 [33]: This match was decided by penalties. Argentina won 6-5.
 [34]: This match was decided by penalties. Argentina won 6-5.
 [35]: Playoff.
 [36]: It was got in contest the Province of Buenos Aires Cup.
 [37]: This match was decided by penalties. Brazil won 4-2.
 [38]: It was got in contest the Bank of Mendoza Cup.
 [39]: This match was decided by penalties after extra time. Argentina won 4-3.
 [40]: This match was decided by penalties. Brazil won 4-2.
 [41]: This match was decided by penalties after extra time. Argentina won 6-5.
 [42]: This match was decided by penalties after extra time. Germany won 4-2.
 [43]: El seleccionado argentino es Sub-23 con refuerzos, en la previa de los Juegos Olímpicos de Beijing.
       El partido estaba pautado originalmente para la selección dirigida por Alfio Basile, 
       pero la AFA decidió enviar al Sub-23 en su representación, y así lo entiende la FIFA, 
       por lo tanto se considera "Partido Internacional A".

